title: Creating a screen saver in microsoft visual studio.net 2003
content:
hooray! my mum has started a course at deakin uni, & next thing you know she gets a free copy of microsoft visual studio.net 2003, she said i could also use it, now i would like to create a animated image screen saver out of it, is visual studio the same as visual basic? i have searched under visual studio & got nothing, but i searched under visual basic & got quite a few results, can i use vb under visual studio? can somebody help me find a tutorial or example code or anything that can help me?

btw: i will recreate billy's blaze journey through the worlds of commander keen with vs, if anyone can help me. if those who don't know what i'm talking about, it is a screen saver with all the worlds from all 7 keen games[url=http://www.johnhowardlies.com]Visit JOHNHOWARDLIES.COM to expose the lies about the howard government[/url]
